The following features can be implemented but not implemented for now. How far should it be implemented?

### Nested snippet expansion

This feature allows expanding the snippet even if the user has already in another snippet.
Typically, the two snippets will be merged as one snippet session and the user can jump to all merged placeholders.

### Squash nested placeholders

This feature is only for nested placeholders. For example, the placeholder of the `extends Parent` can be removed with `<BS>`. In this case, another snippet engine (e.g. vim-vsnip) will remove the `Parent` placeholders.

```
class ${1:Class}${2: extends ${3:Parent}} {
  constructor($4) {
    $0
  }
}
```
